questions.question: Who do you admire most in the world and why?
questions.answer: My parents for setting the bar when it comes to relationships as far as I'm concerned.

questions.question: If you could be someone else just for one day, who would it be and why?
questions.answer: Maybe Matt Lauer so I could help people start their day off on the right foot. He seems like a genuine guy and a class act.

questions.question: What is your greatest achievement to date?
questions.answer: Probably the 10 years I have spent as a basketball coach, volunteering and working with inner city kids.

questions.question: If you could watch any movie right now, what would it be, and why?
questions.answer: Probably Wedding Crashers. Perfect flick to wind down to.

questions.question: Who are your top 3 favorite groups/artists and why?
questions.answer: Justin Timberlake, Train, John Mayer. All three have gone their own route and still stood the test of time.

questions.question: Do you prefer team sports or solo sports, and why?
questions.answer: Team sports. I've always thought they are a good metaphor for life.

questions.question: What is the most romantic present you have ever given? Why?
questions.answer: Lingerie. I knew I was in love once I found myself shopping at Victoria Secret.

questions.question: What's the craziest place you had sex?
questions.answer: The balcony of a cruise ship.

questions.question: What's your worst date memory?
questions.answer: I went on one Tinder date a few years back. Right away I realized why I wasn't the online dating type.

questions.question: If you could have one superpower, what would it be and why?
questions.answer: Telepathy because it would make dating so much easier.

bio.tattoos: Right arm. It's a scripture in a scroll saying "Let us love not in word or speech but in truth and action."

questions.question: Would you describe yourself more as "the party starter," "the wingman" or "the laid back one?"
questions.answer: " Laid back one.

questions.question: What is the most outrageous thing you have ever done?
questions.answer: Sign a contract to play professional basketball in Bulgaria.

questions.question: If you could have lunch with one person, who would it be and why?
questions.answer: President Obama, because I want to hear what obstacles, hardship and challenges he had to face to attain the highest position in America.

questions.question: Do you like being the center of attention, or do you prefer being more mysterious and why?
questions.answer: Definitely not the center of attention because there is always a reason why people need attention. I'm confident in who I am as a person.

questions.question: Who is your favorite actor and why?
questions.answer: Denzel, because every movie he was in were all classics and for him to act in several different characters is very impressive.

questions.question: What is your favorite television show and why?
questions.answer: Martin, because even though I've seen each episode more than 100x each, it never gets old.

questions.question: If you wanted to approach a man/woman you had never met before, how would you go about it?
questions.answer: Introduce myself and try to win her over with my charm.

questions.question: What's your biggest date fear?
questions.answer: One of my friends hooking up with my date in the past.

questions.question: Do you follow a specific diet?
questions.answer: Paleo.

questions.question: What is the most outrageous thing you have ever done?
questions.answer: Live four months without power. Cold showers are no joke.

questions.question: What is your greatest achievement to date?
questions.answer: Dominating my basketball league after college. I was Kobe back then.

questions.question: Do you have a serious fear of any kind of animal?
questions.answer: Spiders

questions.question: What do you hope to get out of participating in this television show?
questions.answer: Discovered. Everyone tells me I'm made for TV/movies. Doesn't mean I'm out here hoping for that, but I would like to break into writing or acting.

questions.question: Do you like to go out dancing? If yes, what is your preferred type of dancing?
questions.answer: Salsa. I love spinning the girls.

questions.question: How would you describe yourself as a lover?
questions.answer: Good. I like to take care of my lady first.

questions.question: Do you consider yourself a romantic and why?
questions.answer: Kinda. I don't mind being romantic, but it can show you're weak.

questions.question: If you could have lunch with one person, who would it be?
questions.answer: Elon Musk. I'm a fan of his fearlessness.

questions.question: Gluten?
questions.answer: I'm going to dress up as that for Halloween.

questions.question: What is your favorite memory from your childhood?
questions.answer: Meeting the Power Rangers.

questions.question: What kind of music do you listen to most often?
questions.answer: Rap and country. Yes, you read that correctly.

questions.question: Do you prefer "hot spot" type clubs or low-key bars, and why?
questions.answer: Hot spot clubs because I like to dance.

questions.question: Style-wise, would you say you are satisfied with the way you look, or would you be up for a change? (hair, make-up, clothes)
questions.answer: (hair, make-up, clothes) Hair could use some work.

questions.question: What's the wildest thing you've done in the bedroom?
questions.answer: One word: Tabasco.

questions.question: What does being married mean to you?
questions.answer: A bond for life, being with my best friend and someone I can grow with.

questions.question: How long does it take for you to get ready to go out for a big night on the town
questions.answer: An episode of Seinfeld.

questions.question: How important is your family's approval to you when it concerns dating a certain someone?
questions.answer: Very important. When you get married, you marry the family as well. And that works both ways.

bio.tattoos: Shoulder – family knot, arm – cross, ribs – Ironman, chest – a buck    Do you have any phobias that would prohibit your participation in certain activities? Heights and deep water. Deep water is less of a problem. I want to cage dive with great whites. Standing on a cliff though… NOPE!    What is the best trip you have ever been on and why? I moved to Athens, Greece for modeling for three months. It was everything! I saw the world, made friends, was forced to grow up and be self-sufficient. Learned a lot!    What is your ideal mate's personality like? Intelligent, kind, hard-working, motherly, mature, sophisticated, driven    What's the closest you have ever come to being married? My ex of two years. I was looking at rings after just three months.    If you could watch any movie right now, what would it be, and why? Saving Private Ryan. The storyline is incredible. It's got excitement, love, sadness, tragedy, happiness, everything.    Tell us a fun story about a one night stand. I woke up naked on the cold floor of a pitch-black room. Thought I had been abducted. Then there was a knock and a woman's voice at the door. "Are you ok?" she asked. I asked her to open the door. Turns out it was a girl I had known for a while in the bar scene. I was on the floor of her bathroom where I passed out after going home with her. I was 19 or 20.    What is your greatest achievement to date? Three Ironmans. One on a broken foot.    Who do you admire most in the world and why? My brother. He is intelligent, hard-working and the very best father and husband that I have ever known. He is a rock.    If you could be someone else for just one day, who would it be and why? A professional football player. It is my favorite sport with an awesome paycheck. They're superstars for playing a sport, a game. It just seems so easy.    What is your favorite television show and why? Modern Family. It's hilarious and carefree.
